def df_overview(df):
    print('\n  \n')
    df.info()
    print('\n  ')
    display(df.head())
    if df.duplicated().sum()== 0:
        print('\n     ')
    else:
        print('\n     {}\n'.format(df.duplicated().sum()))
    n = 0    
    for i in df.columns:
        if df[i].isna().sum() != 0:
            print('\n    {} - {}'.format(i, df[i].isna().sum()))
            n += 1
    if n != 0:
        print('     {} '.format(n))
    else:
        print('     ')
        
    print('\n   ')
    display(df.describe().T)

In [13]:
def make_predictions(m, X_train, y_train, X_test, y_test):
    model = m(random_state=0)
    model.fit(X_train, y_train)
    y_pred = model.predict(X_test)
    y_proba = model.predict_proba(X_test)[:, 1]
    print('\tAccuracy: {:.2f}'.format(accuracy_score(y_test, y_pred)))
    print('\tPrecision: {:.2f}'.format(precision_score(y_test, y_pred)))
    print('\tRecall: {:.2f}\n'.format(recall_score(y_test, y_pred)))

clusters = gym_data['cluster_km_new'].sort_values().unique()
print('         \n')
for number, column in enumerate(selected_columns):
    print(f'   {plot_names[number]}    ')
    plt.subplots(figsize=(20,5), sharey=True)
    for plot_num, cluster in enumerate(clusters):
        ax = plt.subplot(1, len(clusters), plot_num+1)    
        sns.histplot(
            data=gym_data.query('cluster_km_new == @cluster'),
            x=column,
            stat='probability',
            common_norm=False,
            #hue='cluster_km',
            bins=10,
            kde = True,
            alpha=0.7                   
        )
